external_knowledge:
- Average yield refers to the mean yield value for each crop across different sites and conditions; 
- Yield is a critical parameter in agriculture, representing the quantity of a crop produced per unit area; 
- The query's focus on average yield suggests an interest in comparing crop productivity or efficiency across various sites and conditions.

sql:
SELECT AVG(avg_yield_value) AS overall_average_yield
FROM (
    SELECT cy.dataset_id, AVG(cy.yield_value) AS avg_yield_value
    FROM crop_yields cy
    GROUP BY cy.dataset_id
) AS avg_yield_per_dataset;

SELECT crop_name
FROM crops
ORDER BY crop_name ASC;

